  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Study examines the molecular basis of food allergy.  It explores the interaction between
      T cells, InKT cells and cytokines in the development of food allergy.  The study also
      explores these factors in development of tolerance &quot;outgrowing&quot; food allergy.  It will also
      explore the genetic factors that lead to the development of food allergy.

      The study examines all type of food allergy including IgE mediated reactions, Eosinophilic
      Esophagitis and Food Protein Induced Enterocolitis
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
